Subject: CardConnect and SkyTab

All,

I hope that things are well.   I very much enjoyed our
meeting with [redacted] last week.   Shift4
is looking forward to moving ahead quickly with the
CardConnect certification.   I believe the best way
to achieve that is by meeting with the Pay at the
Table ("PATT") project managers.  What is the best
way to schedule that?

As you know, Shift4 views Pay-at-the-Table solutions to
be mission critical.  It is an essential component to
our overall product offering.  Our current PATT
strategy is heavily reliant on Ingenico.   Given
Ingenico's acquisition of [redacted], we believe
a new partnership is extremely important.   The
combined Ingenico / [redacted] poses a threat to
Shift4 DOLLARS ON THE NET gateway and
creates significant pricing concerns.   We do see
CardConnect and First Data as a great fit for this new
partnership.

We also wanted to make you aware that Shift4
recently launched a new PATT product called SkyTab
(skytab.com).   SkyTab integrates seamlessly with
many of the leading restaurant POS systems and
utilizes a customized version of the [redacted]
hardware.   There is a photo attached to this email.
We do believe that SkyTab is simply a superior
product when compared to the PATT competition
offered by [redacted]. This has been
validated by independent assessments.

We do have a significant concern about the joint
venture relationship between CardConnect and
[redacted]. [Redacted] is our largest
competitor.   We are also concerned about the
[redacted]. We wanted to mention
this "elephant in the room" in the very beginning of our
certification engagement.   We believe a formal
commitment from CardConnect to allow Shift4 to
certify our own encryption (including P2PE) to run on
the SkyTab device will effectively address this
concern.   We also do not believe the CardConnect/
[redacted] joint venture to be relevant should the
certification of SkyTab run on Shift4 encryption.   We
would appreciate your thoughts on this matter.

We look forward to our next call.

Best Regards,

[Redacted]
Shift4
